#To Add User

sudo useradd username #adding a user

sudo passwd username #assigning him a password **make sure that the username will be same in both the commands

sudo useradd -d /home/username -m username #adding a user with a home directory
where -d option is for directory path and -m option is for creating this directory

sudo deluser username #deleting a user

sudo rm -r /home/username #deleting a home directory of a user which you have deleted

#To Add User (Alternative Command)

sudo adduser username #add a user alongwith password, home directory and other details 


Information of all the users are stored in this file => /etc/passwd

Password of each user is stored in this file in Encrypted form => /etc/shadow


